<xsd:simpleType name="DurationType">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
Limited version of duration that allows for precise time arithmetic. Only Month, Day, Hour, Minute Second terms should be used. Milliseconds should not be used. Year should not be used. Negative values allowed. e.g. PT1004199059S", "PT130S", "PT2M10S", "P1DT2S", "-P1DT2S".
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:restriction base="xsd:duration"/>
</xsd:simpleType>
<xsd:simpleType name="PositiveDurationType">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Limited version of duration. Must be positive.</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:restriction base="DurationType"/>
</xsd:simpleType>
